WEBVTT

00:00.083 --> 00:01.483
<b>1x05 - Have I Got a Deal for You</b>

00:01.584 --> 00:03.545
<i>Come on! Hit him harder!</i>

00:03.586 --> 00:05.506
Smash him good!

00:07.549 --> 00:09.009
Shocksquatch: [ grunts ]

00:09.051 --> 00:10.552
<i>Whoo!</i>

00:10.594 --> 00:13.222
Shocksquatch: Rrrrrrrah!

00:17.226 --> 00:18.810
Rrrrrrrrr...

00:18.810 --> 00:20.354
Unh!

00:20.437 --> 00:22.356
[ crowd cheers ]

00:25.609 --> 00:27.528
Unnnnnh!

00:31.031 --> 00:36.161
Just hand me your new Omnimatrix, Ben
Tennyson, and this can all be over.

00:36.245 --> 00:39.706
Shocksquatch: Well, sure.
Since you asked so nicely.

00:44.711 --> 00:46.463
[ grunts ]

00:50.884 --> 00:52.135
Ohh!

00:54.012 --> 00:57.266
Shocksquatch: Oh, geez.
Don't mention it.

00:57.808 --> 01:01.603
Hokestar: Say there, my good
fellow, could I interest you in ...

01:01.687 --> 01:03.564
[ gasps ]

01:03.605 --> 01:07.693
Ma'am, I can see that a lovely
creature such as yourself ...

01:07.734 --> 01:10.237
[ deep voice ]
Not interested.

01:10.279 --> 01:13.198
Hokestar: My apologies, sir.

01:14.241 --> 01:17.619
Ooh. Why, it looks to me that
you may be in need of a ...

01:17.661 --> 01:19.580
[ speaking alien language ]

01:19.621 --> 01:24.543
Hokestar: What has so
distracted you poor suckers?

01:25.919 --> 01:27.379
Jackpot.

01:27.421 --> 01:29.548
[ both grunting ]

01:31.000 --> 01:37.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:38.682 --> 01:41.935
Shocksquatch: Last chance for
you to quit while you're ahead.

01:41.977 --> 01:44.188
Last chance for you to keep
your head.

01:44.229 --> 01:45.564
Shocksquatch: [ chuckles ]

01:45.606 --> 01:47.900
That was like a joke, but
smaller.

01:47.941 --> 01:50.110
Aah!

01:50.194 --> 01:52.654
Shocksquatch: Aaaaaaah!

01:52.738 --> 01:55.282
This isn't over!

01:55.324 --> 01:56.116
[ beep ]

01:56.200 --> 01:59.203
Ben: Looks to me like is!

01:59.244 --> 02:02.206
<i>Hokestar: Congratulations, my boy!</i>

02:02.247 --> 02:03.624
<i>I saw what you just did.
Wonderful!</i>

02:03.665 --> 02:07.044
Wonderful. Yes, indeed.
Absolutely superlative.

02:07.085 --> 02:10.756
But if you want to prevent
that run-down feeling after

02:10.797 --> 02:12.883
transforming from beast to boy,

02:12.925 --> 02:18.138
what you need is a bottle of
Professor Hokestar's miracle elixir!

02:18.222 --> 02:19.940
Ben: Who with the what, now?

02:20.041 --> 02:21.841
<i><font color=#ca> sync & correction by f1nc0
~ addic7ed.com ~ </font></i>

02:22.105 --> 02:22.689
<i>♪ Ben 10 ♪</i>

02:22.731 --> 02:24.399
<i>♪ he's a kid, and he wants to have fun ♪</i>

02:24.399 --> 02:27.027
<i>♪ but when you need a superhero,
he gets the job done ♪</i>

02:27.068 --> 02:27.569
<i>♪ Ben 10 ♪</i>

02:27.610 --> 02:29.571
<i>♪ with a device that he wears on his arm ♪</i>

02:29.612 --> 02:31.865
<i>♪ he can change his shape and
save the world from harm ♪</i>

02:31.948 --> 02:34.200
<i>♪ when trouble's taking place ♪
♪ he gets right in its face ♪</i>

02:34.242 --> 02:35.578
<i>♪ Ben 10 ♪</i>

02:36.619 --> 02:39.039
<i>♪ when lives are on the line ♪
♪ it's hero time ♪</i>

02:39.080 --> 02:40.398
<i>♪ Ben 10 ♪</i>

02:41.119 --> 02:44.622
Hokestar: This is the
opportunity of a lifetime!

02:44.706 --> 02:51.796
Professor Blarney T. Hokestar's
miracle elixir will change everything!

02:51.838 --> 02:55.550
Ben: Yeah... thanks,
but no, thanks.

02:58.511 --> 03:01.639
Hokestar: [ mutters ]
And how about you, my friends?

03:01.639 --> 03:07.520
Do you, too, doubt the voracity of my
fantastic formula's amazing attributes?

03:07.562 --> 03:09.105
What's that you say?
What's that?

03:09.147 --> 03:11.900
You demand a brief demonstration?

03:11.941 --> 03:13.193
[ aliens murmur ]

03:13.276 --> 03:15.111
<i>Get a job, ya bum!</i>

03:15.153 --> 03:21.201
Hokestar: Then might I have an
able-bodied volunteer from the audience?

03:21.284 --> 03:25.372
<i>If you please, somebody?
Anybody?</i>

03:25.455 --> 03:27.791
Uh, I-I'll do it.

03:27.832 --> 03:29.459
Hokestar: Excellent, my boy.

03:29.542 --> 03:32.295
Splendid. A perfect specimen.
Yes, indeed.

03:32.337 --> 03:37.592
Now, just for clarity's sake,
we've never met before, have we?

03:37.675 --> 03:43.098
N-No, boss ...
I-I mean, professor. We have not.

03:43.139 --> 03:46.184
Hokestar: And your name, my good sir?

03:46.226 --> 03:49.479
They call me Plugg ...
Solid Plugg.

03:49.521 --> 03:50.814
Hokestar: Yeah, of course you
are, dear boy.

03:50.855 --> 03:56.486
And now, are you ready to have
your world forever transformed?

03:58.238 --> 03:59.489
Sure. Why not?

03:59.489 --> 04:03.660
Hokestar: Just sprinkle a few
drops of my miracle elixir on

04:03.702 --> 04:10.834
your scalp, rub vigorously, and in
a mere matter of moments... voilá !

04:10.917 --> 04:14.379
A rich, full head of...
flowers!

04:14.421 --> 04:15.964
[ chuckles nervously ]
Yes, yes.

04:16.005 --> 04:17.966
And not even in season,
don't you know.

04:18.007 --> 04:21.344
Uh, um, yeah, um, uh...
it is a miracle.

04:21.344 --> 04:27.225
I was bald merely moments ago,
and now, forsooth, I am not.

04:27.267 --> 04:28.977
[ wind whistles ]

04:29.018 --> 04:32.605
Hokestar: Now, who will be
the next among you to partake of

04:32.647 --> 04:37.569
my miracle elixir, huh?
Only two taydens a bottle.

04:37.610 --> 04:39.738
Oh, not bad.

04:39.779 --> 04:42.949
I'll take one.
- I'll take two.

04:45.702 --> 04:49.497
Hokestar: As you can see,
my boy, business is booming.

04:49.539 --> 04:51.541
Ben: Doesn't prove a thing.

04:51.583 --> 04:54.419
Like they say, there's
one born every minute.

04:54.461 --> 04:57.881
Hokestar: Oh, well, t...
there's nothing I appreciate

04:57.964 --> 05:00.717
better than the
challenge of a hard sell.

05:00.759 --> 05:01.593
[ chuckles ]

05:01.676 --> 05:05.180
Allow me to try and
change your tiny mind, hmm?

05:05.221 --> 05:06.806
Ben: You're wasting your time.

05:06.890 --> 05:10.310
Hokestar: But it's my time to
waste, now, isn't it?

05:14.606 --> 05:16.691
Welcome, welcome, welcome

05:16.733 --> 05:21.321
to Professor Blarney T. Hokestar's
extraterrestrial emporium, lad.

05:21.362 --> 05:25.325
If you cannot find it here,
it probably doesn't exist.

05:25.367 --> 05:27.327
[ click ]

05:30.455 --> 05:33.166
Ben: Seems like it's just a
bunch of old second-rate ...

05:33.249 --> 05:34.751
[ gasps ]

05:34.793 --> 05:38.088
Where did you get this
"Sumo Slammers" action figure?!

05:38.171 --> 05:39.964
I've never seen one like it before.

05:40.006 --> 05:43.551
Hokestar: Special limited
edition only available from the

05:43.635 --> 05:46.805
concessionaires of Budokan.
Fewer than 100 ever made.

05:46.846 --> 05:51.101
If you like it, it's yours, my
boy, with my compliments.

05:51.142 --> 05:52.435
Ben: Why so generous?

05:52.477 --> 05:55.688
Hokestar: Oh, it wouldn't be the
worst thing in the universe to have

05:55.772 --> 06:01.444
a one-man superhero team as a
spokesman for my elixir, now, would it?

06:01.486 --> 06:04.072
Ben: I guess you and your
stuff may look kind of weird,

06:04.114 --> 06:08.535
but it all seems harmless enough.
Let me think about it.

06:08.576 --> 06:12.455
Hokestar: Oh, that's all I ask, my lad.

06:12.497 --> 06:15.125
[ sumo slammer squeaks ]

06:15.166 --> 06:19.754
How'd it go, professor?
Did you get him?

06:19.796 --> 06:24.718
Hokestar: Patience, Plugg.
He'll come around.

06:24.759 --> 06:26.177
[ beeping ]

06:26.219 --> 06:27.846
<i>Ben: Rook. You there?
It's Ben.</i>

06:27.887 --> 06:29.639
Rook: How did it go with sunder?

06:29.681 --> 06:31.975
Ben: Quick.
He had to catch a flight.

06:32.016 --> 06:35.937
<i>Hey, can you look up a Professor
Blarney T. Hokestar on the extranet?</i>

06:35.979 --> 06:37.939
Rook: Certainly.

06:41.568 --> 06:46.531
Professor Blarney T. Hokestar ...
an intergalactic flimflam man.

06:46.573 --> 06:49.325
The plumbers don't consider
him a threat. Why do you ask?

06:49.367 --> 06:52.328
Ben: Long story.
I just ran into him.

06:52.370 --> 06:53.663
I guess it's not that long.

06:53.705 --> 06:55.665
Rook: Well, should you need backup...

06:55.749 --> 06:57.667
<i>Ben: I promise I'll call you.
Later.</i>

06:57.751 --> 06:58.585
[ beep ]

06:58.626 --> 07:00.587
[ imitating sumo fighter ]

07:04.299 --> 07:04.758
Huh?

07:04.841 --> 07:08.845
Ben Tennyson?
I've been looking for you.

07:08.887 --> 07:12.348
Ben: Yeah?
Well, you just found me.

07:12.390 --> 07:15.852
You're the guy that turns into
different aliens, right, dude?

07:15.935 --> 07:18.480
Saving the universe is your thing.

07:18.521 --> 07:19.731
Ben: Uh-Huh.

07:19.773 --> 07:22.442
Then you, of all people,
should care that Hokestar's

07:22.484 --> 07:25.028
holding a poor, harmless alien hostage!

07:25.070 --> 07:28.281
Keeping it in deplorable
conditions, milking it for that

07:28.448 --> 07:33.036
so-called "professor's"
so-called "miracle elixir," man!

07:33.078 --> 07:35.789
Ben: Did you say "milking"?

07:39.542 --> 07:42.337
Professor? You home?

07:42.420 --> 07:45.799
Nobody here.
We'll have to come back later.

07:45.882 --> 07:47.592
Dude, you just can't give up.

07:47.675 --> 07:50.804
There's a captive creature in
there, and it needs our help!

07:50.887 --> 07:52.889
Like, right now!

07:55.767 --> 07:57.227
Ben: You'd better be right.

07:57.268 --> 07:58.937
[ beep ]

07:58.978 --> 08:01.523
[ laughs ]
Sweet!

08:04.067 --> 08:05.985
Spidermonkey: [ chatters ]

08:08.571 --> 08:10.323
We really shouldn't be in here.

08:10.365 --> 08:11.157
[ chatters ]

08:11.241 --> 08:14.536
So try not to touch anything, okay?

08:24.838 --> 08:28.007
What did I tell you?
This place is a horror show.

08:28.049 --> 08:30.802
Spidermonkey: Eh.
More like a sideshow.

08:30.844 --> 08:33.638
But it sure is creepy.
That, I'll give you.

08:33.722 --> 08:35.181
[ chatters ]

08:35.265 --> 08:39.102
So, where's this poor captive
creature that you're so worried about?

08:39.144 --> 08:41.187
[ tone sounds ]

08:41.229 --> 08:42.772
Aah! Whoa!

08:42.813 --> 08:46.609
Never mind. I think I found it.

08:46.651 --> 08:48.653
Meet the Screegit ...

08:48.737 --> 08:52.782
one of the most endangered
species in the whole universe.

08:52.782 --> 08:54.909
[ squeaks ]

08:54.951 --> 08:56.703
[ yawns ]

08:56.745 --> 08:59.581
Ben: Aww! It's adorable!

08:59.622 --> 09:00.290
[ chatters ]

09:00.331 --> 09:04.919
Ben: Who's a cute widdle guy?
You are! Yes, you are!

09:04.961 --> 09:07.922
Hey, man. That's not cool.
Don't talk down to him.

09:07.964 --> 09:09.340
Ben: [ clears throat ]

09:09.382 --> 09:12.552
Sorry.
What's with the energy globe?

09:12.635 --> 09:14.554
This.

09:30.612 --> 09:34.991
Ben: O-Kay. That's disgusting.
- I know, right?!

09:35.033 --> 09:38.661
Hokestar's using and abusing
this poor creature for profit.

09:38.745 --> 09:43.208
All of nature's creatures deserve
to know what freedom looks like!

09:43.249 --> 09:44.876
Free the Screegit!

09:44.876 --> 09:46.544
Free the Screegit!

09:46.586 --> 09:49.714
<i>Hokestar: Freeze, you
miserable miscreants!</i>

09:49.714 --> 09:54.552
Move a muscle, and I will
blast you where you ...

09:54.594 --> 09:56.137
Ohh!

09:56.179 --> 09:57.222
[ weapon cocks ]

09:57.305 --> 09:58.848
Ben: Aah!

10:09.988 --> 10:12.282
Ben: What did you do?!

10:12.324 --> 10:14.993
Hokestar: Egads!
He just ran right out in front of me!

10:15.076 --> 10:17.287
I-I-I-I-I-I didn't mean to!
I, uh ...

10:17.329 --> 10:19.289
[ gasps ]

10:30.258 --> 10:34.137
Whoa! That was a rush!

10:34.179 --> 10:35.805
[ blows ]

10:35.889 --> 10:39.267
Hokestar: My boy, oh, I-I
cannot begin to make proper

10:39.309 --> 10:42.395
amends for my accidental
act of minor mayhem. I ...

10:42.437 --> 10:45.649
Ben: You can start by putting
that thing away!

10:47.776 --> 10:49.527
Hokestar: [ sighs ]

10:49.569 --> 10:50.654
Oh, yes, yes.

10:50.737 --> 10:55.367
Now, if I might be so bold as to
ask what precisely are you two

10:55.408 --> 10:59.329
rapscallions doing in my
ship in the first place?

10:59.371 --> 11:03.333
You know perfectly well who
I am and what I'm doing here.

11:04.167 --> 11:06.378
Hokestar: Eh...
refresh my memory.

11:06.419 --> 11:11.132
I'm Pax, alien-rights activist.
- Ben: Wait. What?

11:11.174 --> 11:12.133
[ clears throat ]

11:12.175 --> 11:15.971
And we're here to free the poor
Screegit from its life of torment.

11:16.012 --> 11:17.389
Hokestar: Torment?!

11:17.430 --> 11:21.184
My boy, I am merely doing the
Screegit a kindness.

11:21.226 --> 11:23.770
Like Earth cows, the milk in its

11:23.812 --> 11:28.149
system needs to be relieved
with startling regularity.

11:28.191 --> 11:30.360
What kind of fools do you take us for?

11:30.402 --> 11:32.863
Hokestar: What are my options?

11:32.946 --> 11:35.323
Ben: Uh, Pax, was it?

11:35.365 --> 11:37.742
This Screegit thing
does seem pretty happy.

11:37.784 --> 11:41.037
More like a pet, really, than a hostage.

11:41.037 --> 11:42.330
What's the difference?

11:42.372 --> 11:45.876
Hokestar: For one, I treat the
Screegit as if he were my own kin.

11:45.917 --> 11:48.169
You keep your family
locked up in a cage?!

11:48.253 --> 11:49.170
Ben: I think ...

11:49.254 --> 11:52.132
Hokestar: It is for his own
safety, of course ... and ours.

11:52.173 --> 11:53.508
Ben: You know, I was ...

11:53.592 --> 11:57.721
You ... you can't do this!
It's, like, a travesty, man!

11:57.762 --> 12:01.099
Hokestar: It's not up to you, radical!

12:01.099 --> 12:04.311
Ben: All right, fine!
Ignore this!

12:06.438 --> 12:10.358
Until I know what's what, the
Screegit's coming with me!

12:11.443 --> 12:13.236
No!
- No!

12:13.278 --> 12:15.697
[ both shout ]

12:15.739 --> 12:16.364
[ thud ]

12:16.406 --> 12:20.243
<i>- Every creature belongs to itself!
- Ben: Give me that back!</i>

12:20.327 --> 12:23.496
Hokestar: No! No! Gimme!
It's mine!

12:23.538 --> 12:25.749
Not again! Nuh-Uh!

12:25.790 --> 12:28.710
What the boss wants, the boss gets!

12:28.752 --> 12:31.796
[ all grunting ]

12:31.880 --> 12:33.798
[ growls ]

12:36.092 --> 12:37.260
Ben: [ groans ]

12:37.260 --> 12:38.428
[ coos ]

12:38.428 --> 12:41.973
Ben: You're gonna be
really sorry you did that.

12:42.057 --> 12:44.935
[ beep ]

12:44.976 --> 12:47.187
[ electricity crackles ]

12:47.270 --> 12:50.106
Aaaaaaaah!

12:50.106 --> 12:51.274
[ thud ]

12:51.358 --> 12:53.985
Ooh!

12:54.069 --> 12:55.820
[ laughs ]

12:55.904 --> 12:57.364
Tickles.

12:57.447 --> 13:01.201
Ampfibian: Just my luck.

13:01.243 --> 13:04.120
[ electricity crackles ]

13:04.120 --> 13:05.288
[ chuckles ]

13:05.330 --> 13:07.290
My turn.

13:13.421 --> 13:15.131
[ squeals ]

13:18.301 --> 13:20.136
Ohh!

13:20.178 --> 13:22.806
Ampfibian: All yours, tough guy.

13:22.889 --> 13:23.473
[ beep, beep ]

13:23.557 --> 13:25.392
[ sighs ]

13:31.439 --> 13:34.192
Ohh!

13:34.276 --> 13:37.737
Ampfibian: Hang in there.
[ chuckles ]

13:37.779 --> 13:40.657
Get back here, Ben Tennyson!

13:40.699 --> 13:45.161
<i>Solid Plugg's not finished with you!</i>

13:46.204 --> 13:50.500
Hokestar: You have no idea
what you're doing, my boy!

13:50.542 --> 13:55.380
Bring back the Screegit!
- No, no! Free the Screegit!

13:59.009 --> 14:01.845
Ampfibian: Yeah, I'm on my
way in right now, Rook, and I've

14:01.887 --> 14:03.346
got some rare Screegit with me.

14:03.388 --> 14:06.558
<i>Rook: You have a Screegit?!
On Earth?!</i>

14:06.600 --> 14:10.770
Ampfibian: Well, I took it from
a couple of aliens for safekeeping.

14:10.812 --> 14:13.106
It's no big ...
[ glass shatters ]

14:13.148 --> 14:16.776
[ moaning ]

14:16.860 --> 14:20.405
[ beeping ]

14:20.447 --> 14:21.865
[ people screaming ]

14:21.948 --> 14:23.325
[ horn blares ]

14:23.366 --> 14:26.203
Ben: Huh?

14:26.286 --> 14:27.954
Whoa!

14:28.038 --> 14:29.414
[ moans ]

14:29.497 --> 14:31.208
Ben: What just happened?!

14:31.208 --> 14:35.212
The galaxy's cutest fuzzball is
suddenly looking a lot less cute.

14:35.253 --> 14:37.464
<i>Rook: The Screegit's not just rare.</i>

14:37.505 --> 14:38.882
<i>It's incredibly dangerous.</i>

14:38.965 --> 14:40.342
Ben: You don't say.

14:40.383 --> 14:41.801
<i>Rook: I'm on my way.</i>

14:41.843 --> 14:42.719
[ panting ]

14:42.761 --> 14:44.012
W-where's the Screegit?

14:44.054 --> 14:47.057
Ben: First start by telling
me what happened to it.

14:47.098 --> 14:52.479
I have no idea. I mean, Screegits
usually only react like this in a

14:52.562 --> 14:56.441
nitrogen-filled environment, but
you earthlings breathe oxygen.

14:56.483 --> 15:00.111
Ben: Surprise! Earth's atmosphere
has nitrogen in it, too, pal.

15:00.195 --> 15:03.657
Well, why didn't you tell me?!
- Ben: Why didn't you ask?!

15:03.698 --> 15:06.910
It's not the sort of thing that
just comes up in conversation.

15:06.993 --> 15:08.203
"Oh, hi. My name's Ben.

15:08.286 --> 15:11.039
My atmosphere is rich in
nitrogen. How's yours?"

15:11.081 --> 15:13.041
[ footsteps thudding ]

15:17.420 --> 15:19.756
[ tires screech ]

15:19.798 --> 15:22.175
Aaaaaah!

15:25.804 --> 15:29.933
[ people screaming ]

15:29.975 --> 15:33.937
Please ... you got to stop it.
Without hurting it!

15:33.979 --> 15:35.939
Ben: Yeah. Sure.

15:37.649 --> 15:39.609
[ car alarm blares ]

16:10.765 --> 16:14.603
[ people screaming ]

16:14.644 --> 16:16.438
[ groans ]

16:16.521 --> 16:18.857
[ beeping ]

16:18.940 --> 16:21.192
So, what now, man?

16:21.234 --> 16:24.946
Ben: So, I track him
down and capture him, man!

16:26.698 --> 16:27.824
Come on, Fasttrack.

16:27.866 --> 16:29.409
[ beep ]

16:29.451 --> 16:32.329
Wildmutt: [ growls ]

16:32.370 --> 16:35.332
Why are you a vulpimancer?

16:35.373 --> 16:36.625
Wildmutt: [ growls ]

16:36.708 --> 16:39.419
I don't know, man.
I'd never ride a fellow being.

16:39.502 --> 16:43.590
It's degrading.
This is not right.

16:43.632 --> 16:45.675
Wildmutt: [ growls ]

16:45.717 --> 16:47.260
[ people scream ]

16:47.344 --> 16:51.723
I tell you, man, this day just
keeps getting weirder and weirder.

16:51.723 --> 16:53.892
Wildmutt: [ growls ]

17:08.477 --> 17:12.231
Oh, man! It smashed
right through those tracks!

17:12.271 --> 17:13.648
[ train whistle blows ]

17:13.691 --> 17:16.859
And that makes the problem
substantially worse.

17:16.902 --> 17:18.319
[ beep ]

17:18.362 --> 17:19.445
Ben: [ grunts ]

17:19.488 --> 17:22.700
Oh, come on. Seriously?
Are those keys in your pocket?

17:22.741 --> 17:25.243
Sorry, dude!

17:25.285 --> 17:28.454
Ben: All right, Omnitrix, I need
something big to stop that train.

17:28.497 --> 17:29.248
You hear me?

17:29.289 --> 17:29.790
[ beep ]

17:29.873 --> 17:32.710
Juryrigg: Juryrigg?
How does this help anybody?!

17:32.793 --> 17:33.293
[ beep ]

17:33.335 --> 17:36.672
Grey matter: Grey matter?!
Seriously?

17:36.714 --> 17:37.881
[ beep ]

17:37.965 --> 17:40.592
<i>Nanomech: Oh, come on, already!</i>

17:40.676 --> 17:42.594
[ beep ]

17:45.597 --> 17:47.891
Blox: Oh, is this gonna hurt.

17:47.933 --> 17:52.312
Yaaaaaaah!

17:52.354 --> 17:53.147
Awesome!

17:53.230 --> 17:57.317
Blox: Glad you enjoyed it so much.
- So, what do we do now?

17:57.359 --> 18:01.280
Hokestar: Use your noodle, my boy.
You're a segmentasapien.

18:01.321 --> 18:05.409
Blox: Is that what I am?
I mean... so?

18:05.451 --> 18:08.787
Hokestar: So? [ mutters ]
I have met your kind before!

18:08.871 --> 18:12.332
If you transform your body to
surround the Screegit in an

18:12.416 --> 18:16.045
airtight shell and allow me to
vacuum away the nitrogen, the

18:16.086 --> 18:20.090
little dickens should revert to
a more containable size.

18:20.132 --> 18:23.719
Blox: Okay. Stay back and let
me deal with king fuzzyface.

18:23.761 --> 18:25.804
I'll yell when I'm ready for you.

18:25.804 --> 18:28.182
Hokestar: I am at your beck and call.

18:28.265 --> 18:29.975
Just remember...

18:30.017 --> 18:30.976
[ grunts ]

18:31.018 --> 18:33.520
...it's an innocent, harmless creature!

18:33.562 --> 18:37.608
Blox: Tell that to
the transit authority.

18:37.649 --> 18:39.610
[ people screaming ]

18:44.406 --> 18:49.453
Blox: Hey! Droolmeister!
That's far enough.

18:49.495 --> 18:52.289
[ belches ]

18:52.373 --> 18:53.540
Blox: Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow, ow,

18:53.540 --> 18:54.041
Ow, ow, ow!

18:54.041 --> 18:56.043
Still ow! Ow!

18:59.713 --> 19:02.841
[ sighs ]

19:02.883 --> 19:04.468
Less ow. Ow.

19:04.551 --> 19:05.302
[ grunts ]

19:05.386 --> 19:08.389
Blox: This is not gonna be easy.

19:10.349 --> 19:12.309
[ grunts ]

19:16.021 --> 19:19.650
Sorry to have to do this
to you, big fella. But...

19:19.692 --> 19:24.530
No! As a duly deputized agent of
extraterrestrials for the ethical

19:24.530 --> 19:29.368
treatment of aliens, I cannot
allow you to harm the Screegit!

19:29.451 --> 19:30.327
[ chomps ]

19:30.411 --> 19:35.082
Hey!
I'm on your side, man!

19:35.124 --> 19:36.291
Hokestar: Quick, now!

19:36.333 --> 19:38.919
Before the cursed creature
becomes too big to contain!

19:38.961 --> 19:42.548
Blox: I'm working as
fast as I can, here.

19:42.756 --> 19:44.466
[ car alarm blares ]

19:44.508 --> 19:46.385
[ growls ]

19:46.427 --> 19:48.846
[ glass shatters ]

19:48.887 --> 19:51.598
Please! Leave him alone!

19:51.598 --> 19:53.017
Aah!

19:53.058 --> 19:54.935
Unh!

19:55.019 --> 19:57.021
Blox: Now, professor! Now!

19:57.062 --> 20:00.274
Hokestar: On my way, my boy!

20:00.315 --> 20:01.442
Blox: Hurry!

20:01.483 --> 20:02.151
[ grunts ]

20:02.234 --> 20:03.485
Can't keep this up...

20:03.527 --> 20:04.319
[ grunts ]

20:04.361 --> 20:05.946
...much longer.

20:09.158 --> 20:11.118
[ motor starts ]

20:15.289 --> 20:16.498
Professor?

20:16.582 --> 20:19.209
Hokestar: [ sighs ]
It's over, my lad.

20:19.251 --> 20:21.962
You can let go of it now.

20:22.004 --> 20:24.882
[ beeping ]

20:24.923 --> 20:29.303
There you are, precious.
Back to your rightful form.

20:29.345 --> 20:32.348
No!
The Screegit must run free!

20:32.431 --> 20:34.516
<i>Free the Screegit!</i>

20:34.600 --> 20:36.518
Does this guy ever quit?

20:36.602 --> 20:39.063
Free the ...
Ooh!

20:39.104 --> 20:43.150
Rook: We will take possession of the
creature now, thank you very much.

20:43.233 --> 20:47.780
<i>Go ahead! Lock me away!
Then I'll get to experience how</i>

20:47.821 --> 20:51.825
my caged alien brethren
and sister-en feel.

20:51.867 --> 20:54.411
Ben: So it's a happy ending
for everyone.

20:54.453 --> 20:57.414
Hokestar: Indeed!
And now, with your kind

20:57.456 --> 21:01.627
permission, gentlemen, I shall
take my Screegit and be ...

21:01.668 --> 21:04.546
Ben: Handcuffed to that
nutjob for a year if you so much

21:04.588 --> 21:06.840
as think about touching that Screegit.

21:06.840 --> 21:09.009
Hokestar: Screegit?
W-w-w-what Screegit?

21:09.009 --> 21:11.178
Never heard of the
thing before in my life.

21:11.178 --> 21:12.971
[ chuckles ]
No, indeed.

21:13.013 --> 21:16.642
Now, if you'll forgive my hasty departure,
pleasure to make your acquaintance.

21:16.684 --> 21:21.105
Looking forward to your endorsement
of my products, Ben Tennyson!

21:21.188 --> 21:25.651
Ben: Yeah, like that'll happen.
- Duh... boss?

21:25.734 --> 21:28.904
Rook: The professor's
motives, I can understand.

21:28.946 --> 21:30.823
That Pax fellow ... not so much.

21:30.864 --> 21:34.743
Ben: He means well. Which
makes him even more dangerous.

21:34.743 --> 21:35.994
Rook: Hmm.

21:36.036 --> 21:37.454
[ grunting ]

21:37.496 --> 21:39.665
Boss! Don't leave Plugg!

21:39.748 --> 21:43.252
Plugg can't go back to the hoosegow!

21:43.293 --> 21:45.045
[ plumbers grunt ]

21:45.087 --> 21:47.723
[ grunting ]

21:47.765 --> 21:50.852
Razzle-frazzle
red-spot plumbers!

